commit e5d662dbc2ad5caf53895e891f42ab0281650513
Author: Fabian Deutsch <fabian.deutsch@gmx.de>
Date:   Mon Oct 17 19:59:23 2011 +0200

    toggle: Honor the disabled property.
    
    The toggle button consists of two actors, a handle and a background, the
    disabled property needs to be checked on the toggle and not on the
    background actor.
    
    Signed-off-by: Fabian Deutsch <fabian.deutsch@gmx.de>

 mx/mx-toggle.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

commit be13d3e7d62f95b9e5ffef34b07b22a6c6417df1
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Mon Oct 17 11:44:43 2011 +0100

    action: prevent warnings when using MxAction with glib 2.28
    
    The "name", "parameter-type", "enabled" and "state" properties were
    construct writable in glib 2.28, but not in glib 2.30. Adding them to
    set_property if compiled with a glib version less than 2.30.0 prevents
    warnings when the constructor attempts to set the properties.

 mx/mx-action.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

