commit 84f59cf3ee2728827ea26b697a4f96feba6860f1
Author: Lionel Landwerlin <lionel.g.landwerlin@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 24 21:27:03 2011 +0100

    tooltip: fix crash when giving NULL argument
    
    Signed-off-by: Lionel Landwerlin <lionel.g.landwerlin@linux.intel.com>

 mx/mx-tooltip.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit 52945cfcfc775df627296a594df30aae71fb3dd6
Author: Lionel Landwerlin <lionel.g.landwerlin@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 24 21:30:18 2011 +0100

    image: give correct rowstride argument to cogl_texture_set_region
    
    On the Sodaville platform, we experienced a memory corruption in media
    explorer triggered by Cogl when premultiplying a texture. It turns out
    that we gave a wrong rowstride (8 bytes smaller) to Cogl when calling
    cogl_texture_set_region. Because Cogl relies on rowstride to allocate
    its buffers, but uses width * pixelsize for processing images, we were
    writing 8 bytes behind an allocated buffer and corrupting malloc's
    internal datas.
    
    Signed-off-by: Lionel Landwerlin <lionel.g.landwerlin@linux.intel.com>

 mx/mx-image.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit 3960c63715b0d85997822110a1204ba77a3f13e5
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 7 17:18:30 2011 +0100

    Revert "mx-actor-manager: unparent container before removing children"
    
    This reverts commit 339b5774678b7f68f7453ac427c5ce983af15f5c.
    
    Comment from Bugzilla (#2662):
    
    "Sorry I left an ugly trace in that patch, also their is a bug with
    the callback not being restarted."

 mx/mx-actor-manager.c | 32 +++++++-------------------------
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 25 deletions(-)

