commit 535e6f5d4bd057387723df99551811271ff47102
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Wed May 11 12:25:23 2011 +0100

    adjustment: Change the default step-increment to 1.0
    
    A step-increment of zero produces odd/invalid results when used with
    scroll-bars or the kinetic scroll-view. Change this so it default to a
    more useful value.

 mx/mx-adjustment.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit 61d7ea438e15d321f318ed5214ddd665f6d83a09
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue May 10 21:25:48 2011 +0100

    test-scroll-view: Swallow button events on the scroll-view
    
    Due to behaviour changes in the kinetic scroll-view, dragging inside the
    view was moving the window. Fix this by swallowing button events on the
    scroll-view, so that they don't bubble down to the stage.

 tests/test-scroll-view.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

commit 3aa5ce5490b1b8ce4bd3762ec9f61856e6627693
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue May 10 21:21:19 2011 +0100

    kinetic-scroll-view: Fix non-capture mode
    
    When not using captured events, motion events were still captured before
    the scroll threshold was exceeded, making it a bit less useful. Alter the
    event-handling process so that in non-capture mode, the motion-event
    signal is used instead of the captured-event signal before the scroll
    threshold is exceeded.
    
    This allows embedding horizontally scrolling kinetic scroll-views in
    vertically scrolling ones (and vice-versa).

 mx/mx-kinetic-scroll-view.c | 89 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 77 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-)

commit 9fb62f78e216546c52b867053b9a3b033c079c41
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue May 10 21:18:58 2011 +0100

    widget: Don't swallow all button events
    
    Widget always returns TRUE in button press/release - this is quite awkward
    when you're relying on the events bubble phase for cascading unused
    events. Alter it so that it only returns TRUE when the widget is disabled
    (which is still a bit dubious, but at least more predictable).

 mx/mx-widget.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit e15d644071d049cb424fbbafdf0f575e6ad2ef37
Author: Tomeu Vizoso <tomeu.vizoso@collabora.co.uk>
Date:   Thu Feb 24 19:23:15 2011 +0100

    Add MxKineticScrollView::"scroll-policy"
    
    and use it when determining if the initial drag threshold has
    been passed.
    
    http://bugzilla.clutter-project.org/show_bug.cgi?id=2578

