commit b2d624b52c24b0e36a11e111df7175239ac08783
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 8 14:47:33 2011 +0100

    image: Don't leave priv->old_texture in an invalid state when failing
    
    If an image load fails due to a bad cache request, or a failed texture
    allocation, don't leave the priv->old_texture pointer in an invalid state.

 mx/mx-image.c | 11 +++++++----
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

commit 4cb3fbd096fe0b2629d688fb56a45d58e2d5b338
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 8 12:19:18 2011 +0100

    table: Fix asking for width/height without a for_height/width failing
    
    If you asked a table for its preferred width or height without also
    specifying a for-width/height, it would always return just the minimum
    size.
    
    Fix this by assigning the final-size of the row/column to the preferred
    size by default (this will later be overwritten if a for-width/height is
    specified).

 mx/mx-table.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit bb06b9b87d8407aa0edc5e835428f4d73b5ba8af
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 7 12:36:51 2011 +0100

    actor-manager: Allow instantiation of an actor manager
    
    Allow creation of an actor manager, and delegate the get_for_stage
    function as convenience API. It's possible you may want multiple managers
    on a single stage, and to manage the time-slicing accordingly.

 docs/reference/libmx/mx-sections.txt |  1 +
 mx/mx-actor-manager.c                | 79 +++++++++++++++++++++++-------------
