commit 743c736a2cd95c5c00ca0baaa1e51b8c57b4722b
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Wed Mar 30 14:05:03 2011 +0100

    focus-manager: Handle the current focus disappearing more thoroughly
    
    When the focus becomes unmapped, push focus again on the highest-level
    focusable widget with the prior hint. This works in more cases than
    responding to unparenting and pushing focus on the parent.

