commit 7af082809c3ba1a0f074e2a1e7dae34e14f3027e
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Mon Mar 28 16:31:00 2011 +0100

    image: Fix mx_image_set_from_pixbuf when filename and pixbuf are given
    
    If mx_image_set_from_pixbuf was called with a pixbuf *and* a filename,
    and the file wasn't in the cache, it would bail out instead of using the
    given pixbuf.
    
    This fixes synchronous image loading.

 mx/mx-image.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit 279855fd0a9d1b3bd4aae446f384ba37e91f3431
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Mar 24 16:26:57 2011 +0000

    texture-cache: Simplify the URI/path resolution
    
    Instead of using a crazy all-in-one function with questionable methods,
    use a regex to determine if a string is a URI and just have different paths
    depending on what we want to do.

 mx/mx-texture-cache.c | 138 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------------------
 1 file changed, 74 insertions(+), 64 deletions(-)

commit 9397b683cfc57a1a5a740e3be1155acbc7606d41
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 22 17:26:54 2011 +0000

    image: Use the new MxTextureCache meta-texture storage function
    
    MxImage needs to duplicate its given data/textures and add a 1-pixel
    transparent border around them. This change allows this newly generated
    image to be cached, using the new meta-texture storage functionality of
    MxTextureCache.

 mx/mx-image.c | 353 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------
 mx/mx-image.h |   3 +
 2 files changed, 291 insertions(+), 65 deletions(-)

commit c5448383364532e07cb6f019ed52838f2f72a754
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 22 17:23:46 2011 +0000

    texture-cache: Add the ability to store meta-textures
    
    Add new functions that allow you to store associated texture data with
    URIs.
    
    This is handy if you have a small modification that you need to make to the
    actual texture data for a particular use, but you still want this modified
    texture to be cached and reused between multiple actors.

 mx/mx-texture-cache.c | 215 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----
 mx/mx-texture-cache.h |  18 ++++-
 2 files changed, 218 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)

commit d13b172d7cd1fa51c6b5ac0bf349e724178b71bb
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Wed Mar 16 15:11:49 2011 +0000

    texture-cache: Add mx_texture_cache_insert()
    
    Add a new function, mx_texture_cache_insert(), that lets you pre-seed the
    texture cache with results. This also allows you to insert arbitrary URIs
    into the texture cache, or even allows you to override particular URIs.

 docs/reference/libmx/mx-sections.txt |   1 +
 mx/mx-texture-cache.c                | 108 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++--------
 mx/mx-texture-cache.h                |   4 ++
 3 files changed, 90 insertions(+), 23 deletions(-)

