commit ee257f1dbb7a63eea550de9535ad570fdfbbde2a
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 24 13:16:59 2011 +0000

    stylable: Invalidate the style string correctly
    
    Make sure that the style string is invalidated when any of the properties
    that affect it change. Do this by resetting the style-string qdata inside
    the property-changed notification callback.
    
    This commit has the pleasant side-effect that changing the pseudo-class
    of a stylable won't invalidate its cache unnecessarily.

 mx/mx-stylable.c | 27 ++++++++++++++-------------
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 13 deletions(-)

