commit c0d88602e0fdbc1b46e34e318b197a74fd99821c
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Tue Feb 1 15:24:50 2011 +0000

    adjustment: do not prematurely stop an interpolation
    
    Do not stop the interpolation when the new adjustment value is exactly at
    the end of the adjustment range, since this prevents interpolation down
    from that value. This occurs if the first "new-frame" signal emission on
    the ClutterTimeline is called when the timeline has not yet progressed.

 mx/mx-adjustment.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

