commit e650cc4906784b5ce9870d51516b5b3b11f41680
Author: Emmanuele Bassi <ebassi@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Feb 1 16:03:11 2011 +0000

    build: Use the introspection's Makefile rules
    
    The GObject Introspection projects ships with a nice Makefile template
    that you can include into your own project's autotooling to get nicer
    and standardized rules. This requires a bit of fiddling in order to have
    versioned targets in our own Makefile.am, but it's trivial enough.
    
    In this case, we copied the same setup Clutter uses.

 configure.ac   |  5 ++++-
 mx/Makefile.am | 63 ++++++++++++++++++++++++----------------------------------
 2 files changed, 30 insertions(+), 38 deletions(-)

