commit d8f91c2ddc493fe67cb4f4a391b9d7a30f1992a7
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jan 25 13:52:06 2011 +0000

    image: Make sure to start cross-fades from the beginning
    
    Stop the cross-fade timeline before starting it, so it starts from the
    beginning. This makes interrupted cross-fades look a bit less jarring.

 mx/mx-image.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

commit 389b6e450bcfcb2373c774875eb299f488460c1d
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jan 25 13:42:20 2011 +0000

    image: Add new properties for fine-grained scaling control
    
    Add three new properties:
    
    allow-upscale: Determines whether the image will ever be scaled upwards
                   when loaded with a specified size
    scale-width-threshold: Determines the amount of lee-way allowed before
                           scaling on the x axis
    scale-height-threshold: Same as above for the y axis
    
    This allows a user of MxImage to make tweaks to balance between CPU, GPU
    and memory-use.

 docs/reference/libmx/mx-sections.txt |   6 +
 mx/mx-image.c                        | 338 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 mx/mx-image.h                        |  12 ++
 3 files changed, 305 insertions(+), 51 deletions(-)

commit 8a901fd2a22fb1ae0455060b5fe7d911a57e8cb0
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Mon Jan 24 16:44:27 2011 +0000

    image: Add asynchronous image loading
    
    Add new functions, mx_image_set_from_file{_at_size},
    mx_image_set_from_buffer{_at_size} and a new property, 'load-async'.
    These add the ability to decode and scale images asynchronously, using
    threads. This adds a dependency on gdk-pixbuf (which Clutter will soon
    require anyway).
    
    This also changes MxImage slightly, adding the 1-pixel border in software,
    rather than using offscreen-rendering and the GPU.

 configure.ac                         |   2 +-
 docs/reference/libmx/mx-sections.txt |   5 +
 mx/mx-image.c                        | 738 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----
 mx/mx-image.h                        |  31 +-
 mx/mx-marshal.list                   |   1 +
 5 files changed, 707 insertions(+), 70 deletions(-)

commit a7da49e76408fa22491b7b56d93f637f3caa6262
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Mon Jan 24 12:37:14 2011 +0000

    image: remove extra initial timeline callback
    
    This was necassary because Clutter could run a paint cycle after the
    timeline was started but before the first "new-frame" signal was emitted.
    This has been fixed in Clutter by commit 5c0aaf5.

 mx/mx-image.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

commit 4d67b5e5292f3839248b63e2bb0b56a2dc971771
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Mon Jan 24 12:35:11 2011 +0000

    Always store the last focused actor when moving focus
    
    Always store the actor that the focus is moving 'from', so that the 'prior'
    focus hint will always work as expected.

