commit 60369160bd07ffe0aca3eca13115a5b31328e63d
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jan 11 13:34:18 2011 +0000

    kinetic-scroll-view: Don't assume children have both adjustments
    
    When retrieving the child's adjustments, don't assume that both exist.
    Some scrollable children have only one adjustment, or may choose to create
    their adjustment at a later time.
    
    Fixes http://bugzilla.clutter-project.org/show_bug.cgi?id=2498

 mx/mx-kinetic-scroll-view.c | 198 ++++++++++++++++++++++++--------------------
 1 file changed, 107 insertions(+), 91 deletions(-)

commit 1495dc3e0f1e355b796ef1647cfb1fd8a09f4741
Author: Damien Lespiau <damien.lespiau@intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jan 11 11:43:50 2011 +0000

    dialog: Compile the blur shader when creating the instance
    
    Instead of compiling the shader on show, we compile it once for all when
    creating the instance. This limits blocking when showing the dialog and
    thus let us see more of the animation.

 mx/mx-dialog.c | 84 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-------------------------
 1 file changed, 48 insertions(+), 36 deletions(-)

