commit e44ab52152625f7a9faf81310e30dbce8e7b41d7
Author: Rob Bradford <rob@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Sat Oct 30 00:17:52 2010 +0100

    spinner: Lower the spinner's update priority to match Clutter's redraw
    
    This prevents a priority-inversion and the potential starvation of the actions
    at an idle priority.
    
    Fixes: http://bugzilla.clutter-project.org/show_bug.cgi?id=2387

 mx/mx-spinner.c | 12 +++++++-----
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

commit 0c052a2e8bd4349c81cc2aaa0f017cf2b3eed38a
Author: Neil Roberts <neil@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Wed Oct 6 17:49:18 2010 +0100

    mx-widget: Set the hover state also when the pointer enters a child
    
    The hover pseudo class on an actor is now also set on a widget
    whenever the pointer enters any children of the actor. This is the
    same behaviour as implemented in HTML. The widget tracks this by
    ignoring leave events when the pointer is leaving to a child. The
    actor should still get the final leave event when the pointer leaves
    the child because it should bubble up to the parent.
    
    Previously the enter and leave events would be ignored when the actor
    is marked as disabled. I've removed this because it would break the
    case where the pointer moves to a disabled child actor and then leaves
    both actors without first passing through the parent. I think the code
    isn't necessary anyway because mx_widget_get_pseudo_class forcibly
    overrides the class when the widget is disabled so it shouldn't do any
    harm to set the hover state.
    
    http://bugzilla.clutter-project.org/show_bug.cgi?id=2357

 mx/mx-widget.c | 16 +++++++---------
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

commit ef30ebda2efaa2d8038470df530aff301c5e4576
Author: Neil Roberts <neil@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Nov 25 12:49:10 2010 +0000

    Increase the Clutter version requirement to 1.4.0
    
    Mx will want to use the clutter_actor_contains function to implement
    the hover style for children of a container so we need to depend on
    1.4.0.

 configure.ac | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

