commit 7d725d8171b3338f7d56035fe1383ece1fd2eda8
Author: Lucas Rocha <lucasr@litl.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 15 19:14:50 2010 +0000

    Implement apply_style on widgets needing to set style on internals
    
    Internal children should always use same style instance than their
    parent widget. apply_style is only implemented on widgets that need it,
    i.e., the ones with stylable internal children:
    
    - MxComboBox
    - MxDialog
    - MxExpander
    - MxPathBar
    - MxProgressBar
    - MxScrollBar
    - MxScrollView
    - MxSlider
    - MxToggle
    - MxToolbar
    
    Fixes bug 2312.

 mx/mx-combo-box.c    | 12 ++++++++++++
 mx/mx-dialog.c       | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-expander.c     | 13 +++++++++++++
 mx/mx-path-bar.c     | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-progress-bar.c | 13 +++++++++++++
 mx/mx-scroll-bar.c   | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-scroll-view.c  | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-slider.c       | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-toggle.c       | 13 +++++++++++++
 mx/mx-toolbar.c      | 12 ++++++++++++
 10 files changed, 156 insertions(+)

commit 31bd4b55dc994ee5f32a05b17badd326db06c85c
Author: Lucas Rocha <lucasr@litl.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 15 19:08:55 2010 +0000

    widget: apply style when style instance changes
    
    We were only handling style changes on a currently set style instance.
    However, when set_style is called on a MxWidget, we need to set same
    style instance on all internal stylable children. They should always
    share the same style context. This should be in widget-specific
    apply_style() implementation.

 mx/mx-widget.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

commit 977c9c9f0c483e3c9347e4a4a7051e5cae206e5e
Author: Lucas Rocha <lucasr@litl.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 15 18:18:47 2010 +0000

    widget: add vfunc to apply style
    
    For instance, this is needed to be able to sync style instances on
    composite widget's internal children.

 mx/mx-widget.c | 25 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-widget.h |  9 ++++++++-
 2 files changed, 33 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit 78921d5ec6a99f239c2ae9c8ea05aaaec6a8facb
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
