commit ae81b0603109a09b374d9e704efbc29ba095ae3a
Author: Tomeu Vizoso <tomeu.vizoso@collabora.co.uk>
Date:   Fri Nov 12 11:23:04 2010 +0000

    kinetic-scroll-view: Ensure child has adjustments
    
    When adding a child to an MxKineticScrollView, call
    mx_scrollable_get_adjustments() to ensure that the adjustments have been
    created before allocation has been reached. This fixes the case where
    adding an MxBoxLayout to an MxKineticScrollView can result in unexpected
    behaviour, as its adjustments are initialised in its own allocate
    function. This is analogous to the behaviour of MxScrollView.
    
    Ideally, MxBoxLayout should initialise its adjustments immediately using
    the current allocation box, but there are cases where this may cause
    allocation cycles.

 mx/mx-kinetic-scroll-view.c | 12 +++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit 4779e072b6d82450d5a069b4b78e443988e46a9e
Author: Lucas Rocha <lucasr@gnome.org>
Date:   Sun Oct 10 22:57:34 2010 +0100

    box-layout: fix animation when inserting child between children
    
    When animating to add a new child in between existing children, we still
    have to update current allocation position after allocating the still
    invisible (i.e. opacity = 0) new child.

 mx/mx-box-layout.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

