commit d16ffe8bf4aa1d32b82b31a5ba6826560456d883
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 8 14:12:04 2010 +0000

    offscreen: Use the allocation box to get the size of the actor in paint
    
    When painting, we were using clutter_actor_get_size to get the actor's
    size when painting the accumulation buffer. This doesn't always do what
    you expect, and instead, we want to use the allocation box.

