commit aec8ef914ba32b7283207ae25ba79c9895f328eb
Author: Neil Roberts <neil@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 1 16:49:00 2010 +0000

    Don't compile with *_DISABLE_DEPRECATED
    
    The G_DISABLE_DEPRECATED and CLUTTER_DISABLE_DEPRECATED flags are only
    really intended for debugging and it doesn't make much sense to set
    them in all builds. Even if Mx is not currently using any deprecated
    features the defines may make the build fail with future versions of
    Clutter or glib that would otherwise be backwards compatible.

 mx/Makefile.am | 4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

commit 3b775e39c0e5db367f0c708ecb1142637c256d2d
Author: Damien Lespiau <damien.lespiau@intel.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 28 21:48:13 2010 +0100

    build: Don't hardcode clutter-x11-1.0 in the .pc file
    
    Mx can be built with a "none" winsys for EGL flavours of clutter. Let's
    not hardcode a clutter-x11-1.0 pkg-config dependency in the .pc file but
    just require clutter-1.0 instead.

 mx.pc.in | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

