Date:   Thu Oct 14 18:26:38 2010 +0100

    window: Make sure to reallocate when setting the window child
    
    Force a reallocation when setting the window child. This fixes window
    children appearing in the top-left of the window with their preferred size
    when they're set while the window is visible.

 mx/mx-window.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

commit d010b61830813ebafc304546742f3f843feba842
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 14 18:23:20 2010 +0100

    style: Add a reference on the properties hash-table while using
    
    It's possible for the style cache to be invalidated while it's still
    being used. Avoid invalid memory access by adding a hash-table reference
    around the properties table while it's being used.

 mx/mx-style.c | 8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit 428a997bebd833f5c71e2836de1f7382189df5ef
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 14 18:22:25 2010 +0100

    settings: Move the settings provider creation to constructed vfunc
    
    Creating the settings provider can cause a signal to be fired, causing a
    possible infinite loop when calling mx_settings_get_default for the first
    time. Fix this by moving it to the constructed vfunc, so that the
    constructor singleton variable is set before the provider is created.

 mx/mx-settings.c | 74 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-------------------------
 1 file changed, 41 insertions(+), 33 deletions(-)

commit b07a7f200d7e3ef969341bb58272f82a75f43b02
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 14 18:21:05 2010 +0100

    offscreen: Force an update when setting a parented child
    
    It's possible for an offscreen to be mirroring an actor that's after it in
    the scene-graph, causing the first frame to render blank. Force an update
    to avoid this situation (fixes flickering in MxDialog, for example).

 mx/mx-offscreen.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

