commit 8838fe2de86fca419e9a7297ae372df7b3cb5bba
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 5 13:58:24 2010 +0100

    focus-manager: Change push_focus to use MX_FOCUS_HINT_PRIOR
    
    When the focus is pushed, use the 'prior' focus hint so that the last
    actor that was focused within that actor is focused. Also document this,
    to make it explicit what hint is used.

 mx/mx-focus-manager.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit cff7668b6bf2db07558ecccd75b0e4ecd69b1439
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Sep 30 03:22:15 2010 +0100

    style: Add a style cache
    
    Instead of just storing the last gotten style matches and invalidating it
    as soon as the style changes, store a cache of the last 6 applied styles
    against a unique string representing the matchable properties of the
    stylable object.
    
    Invalidate this cache on map, parent-set, on name-change, when the style
    is set, and when pseudo-class or style-class change. This significantly
    cuts down the amount of necessary look-ups (at the cost of a small
    amount of memory).

 mx/mx-private.h  |   2 +
 mx/mx-stylable.c |  36 +++++++++++++++--
 mx/mx-stylable.h |   3 ++
 mx/mx-style.c    | 116 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--------
 4 files changed, 137 insertions(+), 20 deletions(-)

commit 6f34037e901a8baae50290e396f0a316d4f9bd0b
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Sep 30 00:05:28 2010 +0100

    widget: Cache the widget's 'disabled' state
    
    mx_widget_get_disabled previously had to recurse through the widget
    tree to retrieve the disabled state. As this was called in the
    get_pseudo_class implementation, this caused
    mx_stylable_get_pseudo_class to be quite slow, and as this was called for
    every stylesheet match, this caused significant slow-down when the style
    changed.
    
    Move this recursion to only happen when setting disabled or reparenting,
    and cache the result in the widget private struct.

 mx/mx-widget.c | 91 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------------
 1 file changed, 73 insertions(+), 18 deletions(-)

commit 0c3cd37a74269d1e871aca9fd95f1c92017eb5d1
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Wed Sep 29 16:18:19 2010 +0100

    stylable: Don't force a style-changed emission when setting style
    
    The style-changed signal prototype used to include the old style, but this
    has changed to be flags associated with the emission.
    
    Fix mx_stylable_set_style so that it doesn't end up forcing a recursive
    style-changed emission, and fix the documentation for the signal itself.

 mx/mx-stylable.c | 11 ++---------
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

commit a065eadd134c097f004c6325c3580f2a3df7df5a
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Wed Sep 29 15:58:03 2010 +0100

    style: Cache matched stylesheet properties
    
    Cache the hash-table retrieved from the style on a stylable, and invalidate
    it when the style is changed. This optimises cases where sub-classes of
    widgets that have style properties have their own additional style
    properties.

 mx/mx-private.h  |  2 ++
 mx/mx-stylable.c |  1 +
 mx/mx-style.c    | 60 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----
