commit e898392fddfc1a14d90adbaaa1becdda3f22b492
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Sun Sep 26 17:08:21 2010 +0100

    stack: Allocate non-filled children correctly
    
    If an actor supported width-for-height or height-for-width, setting it not
    to fill in a stack would not work correctly. It may be that we want to fix
    this in mx_allocate_align_fill, as it may affect other containers that use
    this function, but for now, compensate for this in the allocate function
    of MxStack.

 mx/mx-stack.c | 58 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 58 insertions(+)

