commit ebcb4135c0e72b6a36be284c4046d185dc754f14
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Sep 7 16:34:10 2010 +0100

    stack-child: Align parameters in header properly

 mx/mx-stack-child.h | 16 ++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

commit 4ab8a9e9341cd64d5f5f309c1d466d6197ba63c3
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Sep 7 16:04:24 2010 +0100

    stack: Add initial implementation
    
    Add implementation of new widget, MxStack. This is an actor that allows
    you to stack multiple widgets on top of each other, with child properties
    that allow for alignment and fill.
    
    This is similar to ClutterBox with the Bin layout manager, but MxStack will
    not allocate its children a larger size than it is allocated itself.

 mx/Makefile.am      |   4 +
 mx/mx-stack-child.c | 369 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
