Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Sep 2 17:21:41 2010 +0100

    window: Use a new enum for rotation instead of orientation
    
    Add a new enum, MxWindowRotation, that has the 4 available rotations
    defined, instead of overloading MxOrientation. This removes the
    'orientation-reversed' property and replaces 'orientation' with
    'window-rotation'.

