commit 9bce34d76747f3dae0f6e1f4406383cfaa80f221
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Aug 24 15:33:25 2010 +0100

    window-x11: Prefix non-static symbols with an underscore
    
    Prefix non-static symbols with an underscore to make sure that they don't
    get exported with the library.

 mx/mx-window.c         | 2 +-
 mx/x11/mx-window-x11.c | 8 ++++----
 mx/x11/mx-window-x11.h | 6 +++---
 3 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

commit ec922f5e47cc1d8e469c58ecbff2869cce6215c3
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Aug 24 14:24:30 2010 +0100

    window: Remove the base class and add MxNativeWindow
    
    Instead of having an abstract base class that has structs the size of
    a GObject and implementing MxWindow in the backend, implement a base
    MxWindow and have it create an MxNativeWindow object (implemented in the
    backend) to do backend-specific tasks.
    
    This is the same way Clutter does it with ClutterStage and
    ClutterStageWindow.

 mx/Makefile.am         |  10 +-
 mx/mx-application.c    |   2 +-
 mx/mx-native-window.c  |  98 +++++
 mx/mx-native-window.h  |  67 ++++
