commit 0b71e9e7a8253ad513c54e32d86db3fc84cf25dc
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Sun Aug 15 16:06:51 2010 +0100

    window-base: Use g_object_new instead of clutter_stage_new
    
    Create the object explicitly instead of using the convenience function.
    This is necessary to bypass the multiple-stage check on single-window
    backends, as Clutter will always create the default stage.
    
    Work-around suggested by the Clutter maintainer, Emmanuele Bassi.

 mx/mx-window-base.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit 3c9cf6e674b12f24b516a9ef7fc02e5c5f5461c8
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Sun Aug 15 16:04:45 2010 +0100

    application/settings: Add 'small-screen' to MxSettings
    
    Instead of checking for this property in MxApplication with X11 specific
    code, add the property to the MxSettings object and move the X11 specific
    code to the X11 MxSettings implementation.
    
    All window-system specific code (except for startup notification) is now
    contained in the corresponding implementation directory.

 mx/mx-application.c        | 279 ++++++++-------------------------------------
 mx/mx-settings-base.c      |  15 ++-
 mx/mx-stylable.c           |   3 +-
 mx/none/mx-settings-none.c |  15 ++-
