commit a995007d1cdff0ab534fb58bf3c1071b26740765
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Sat Aug 14 10:36:13 2010 +0100

    settings: Make a settings base class and inherit from that
    
    Instead of making MxSettings abstract and extending that for specific
    settings objects, make an MxSettingsBase abstract class and implement the
    MxSettings object in the window system directories, inheriting from that
    for the shared code. This alternative method should maintain API/ABI
    compatibility completely (previous method would break g_object_new and
    extending).

 mx/Makefile.am             |   3 +-
 mx/mx-private.h            |   5 ++
 mx/mx-settings-base.c      | 116 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-settings-base.h      |  64 ++++++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-settings.c           | 116 ------------------------------------
 mx/mx-settings.h           |  16 ++++-
 mx/none/mx-settings-none.c |  80 ++++++-------------------
 mx/x11/mx-settings-x11.c   | 144 ++++++++++++++++-----------------------------
 8 files changed, 271 insertions(+), 273 deletions(-)

