commit 1e2e4cff31c4a20ba1cbb9d40cfc6968f7840dc8
Author: Damien Lespiau <damien.lespiau@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Aug 2 12:50:44 2010 -0400

    winsys: Allow Mx to compile without X
    
    Introduce "window systems". For now 'none' and 'x11' which allows to
    compile Mx for X11 (the default) or for no specific window system (for
    instance if we are compiling against a eglnative version of Clutter.
    
    For now, it's only a few #ifdef's but it might need to be extended
    further if one has to write a Windows backend.

 configure.ac                            |  32 ++-
 mx/Makefile.am                          |  20 +-
 mx/mx-application.c                     |  28 ++-
 mx/mx-clipboard-none.c                  | 160 +++++++++++++
 mx/mx-clipboard-x11.c                   | 387 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 mx/mx-clipboard.c                       | 387 --------------------------------
