commit a24eb3407b6384e99a5551023aca30f99be19c54
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 29 10:04:14 2010 +0200

    finger-scroll: Fix kinetic scrolling
    
    The previous code smiplification actually broke kinetic scrolling entirely.
    Fix and improve the maths involved.

 mx/mx-finger-scroll.c | 37 ++++++++++++++++++++++---------------
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)

commit e6f9deb96ccebed2c3d58fd59cbe54f50f8650da
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 22 09:33:22 2010 +0100

    finger-scroll: Don't use grabs and make event capturing optional
    
    Disable motion events and attach to captured events on the stage, instead
    of using grabs (this is more reliable and plays friendlier with other
    actors).
    
    By default, use button-press-event instead of captured-event to initiate
    the scrolling - captured-event can optionally be turned back on.
    
    Also make the mouse button that initiates the scrolling configurable,
    instead of hard-coding mouse-button 1.

 mx/mx-finger-scroll.c | 183 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----------------
 mx/mx-finger-scroll.h |   8 +++
 2 files changed, 134 insertions(+), 57 deletions(-)

commit d15aa5a4823826e4582c119f3e952826d67bad34
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Sat Jul 10 09:34:41 2010 +0100

    finger-scroll: Make it a stand-alone container
    
    Don't extend MxScrollView, instead extend MxBin and make it possible to use
    MxFingerScroll in the same way you can use MxScrollView. As an added bonus,
    it also implements MxScrollable, so you can pack a FingerScroll into a
    ScrollView if you want scroll-bars (for example).

 mx/mx-finger-scroll.c    | 400 +++++++++++++++++++++++++----------------------
 mx/mx-finger-scroll.h    |   6 +-
 tests/test-scroll-view.c |   8 +-
 3 files changed, 221 insertions(+), 193 deletions(-)

commit 4a48472c3fbae9a57442c701f7889fea1466260b
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 7 18:21:22 2010 +0100

    finger-scroll: Simplify/fix-up a bit
    
    Change the button-release-event handler to have only a single path for the
    kinetic scrolling. Fix snapping so that it snaps to the nearest
    step-increment, but only in the direction of scrolling. Fix the new-frame
    callback to handle skipped frames correctly again.

 mx/mx-finger-scroll.c    | 236 ++++++++++++++++++++---------------------------
 tests/test-scroll-view.c |  26 +++++-
 2 files changed, 123 insertions(+), 139 deletions(-)

