commit 5a8d5ef5a927025f06700297a113f1a2b98c047f
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Mon Jul 19 13:35:43 2010 +0100

    modal-frame: Override ClutterActor->show/hide
    
    Instead of having separate functions, mx_modal_frame_show/hide, override
    the ClutterActor show/hide signal handlers. This allows a user to use
    clutter_actor_show/hide normally instead of the special MxModalFrame
    functions.
    
    MxModalFrame goes through some pains to make sure that after calling
    clutter_actor_hide, the actor immediately registers as hidden, even though
    it isn't until the hiding animation finishes.

 docs/reference/libmx/mx-sections.txt |  2 -
 mx/mx-modal-frame.c                  | 80 ++++++++++++++++++------------------
 mx/mx-modal-frame.h                  |  3 --
 tests/test-modal-frame.c             |  4 +-
 4 files changed, 42 insertions(+), 47 deletions(-)

