commit 7601330ddf9841489145779004870d031b1d4f54
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 6 11:50:20 2010 +0100

    style: Allow both point and pixel font sizes
    
    Change the default font-size to be pixels to restore previous behaviour.
    
    When setting the font-size from MxSettings, the value is converted from
    points to pixels (if necessary).
    
    If 'pt' is used as a suffix in the CSS, the value will be converted from
    points to pixels before setting.

 mx/mx-stylable.c |  8 +++++++-
