commit 75659d91188e4ef66217e50817b1df78a917e749
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 18 12:39:53 2010 +0100

    icon-theme: Make fallback loading recursive
    
    When loading icon theme fallbacks, make sure to load the fallbacks of
    fallbacks. This fixes using the Fedora icon theme, for example, which only
    overrides a few icons, then falls back to Mist, which does the same thing
    and inherits gnome.

 mx/mx-icon-theme.c | 87 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------------
 1 file changed, 60 insertions(+), 27 deletions(-)

commit cb5345a26a5cd07c388e27ee8c125b91770bdb7b
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 18 14:36:50 2010 +0100

    mx-settings: prevent possible recursion during the creation of MxSettings
    
    During the construction of MxSettings, the default values are changed from
    reading the xsettings values. Therefore, the "style-changed" signal may
    be emitted. If a handler on this signal requires MxSettings, recurusion can
    occur because the singleton has not yet been saved. This can be avoided by
    making sure the xsettings client is initialised only after the saving of
    the singleton object. This is acheived by implementing the singleton in
    the object's constructor virtual function, and initialising the xsettings
    client in the constructed signal.

 mx/mx-settings.c | 70 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------------
 1 file changed, 55 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)

commit b1baf885bf05036e1bd66555df676c4d77adf172
