commit cb13c731df6ca2d1b849d550b318b066e591280d
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 15 16:13:26 2010 +0100

    Increase the Clutter version requirement to 1.2.0
    
    MxTextureCache now requires Cogl subtexture support.

 configure.ac | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit fcf9f25bd55e479588b338fd4d7e5f25016614e1
Author: Neil Roberts <neil@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 11 16:39:43 2010 +0000

    mx-texture-cache: Use CoglSubTexture instead of MxSubtexture
    
    Since Clutter 1.1.8 Cogl directly has support for sub textures so we
    can avoid the need for MxSubtexture. This has the advantage that there
    are no differences to applications between textures retrieved from a
    pre-generated cache and those loaded from a file directly. For example
    it should now be possible to use a pre-generated cache image in a
    texture frame.
    
    http://bugs.meego.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2869

 mx/Makefile.am        |   1 -
 mx/mx-subtexture.c    | 576 --------------------------------------------------
 mx/mx-subtexture.h    |  97 ---------
 mx/mx-texture-cache.c | 124 +++--------
 4 files changed, 26 insertions(+), 772 deletions(-)

