commit 397111a1570264bb86810a20df99a57cef9fba9d
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu May 20 16:25:33 2010 +0100

    box-layout: Add 'scroll-to-focused' property
    
    This property allows a user to disable MxBoxLayout's automatic
    scroll-to-the-focused-actor capability. This can be useful if you want
    to maintain control over the position value of the adjustment while
    focus is changing.
    
    Fixes MeeGo Bug #2340

 docs/reference/libmx/mx-sections.txt |  2 ++
 mx/mx-box-layout.c                   | 62 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 mx/mx-box-layout.h                   |  4 +++
 3 files changed, 67 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit fd17427b80586a4239be4e2a3fb99237b6049a5e
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Thu May 27 20:23:24 2010 +0100

    offscreen: Add accumulation buffer capability
    
    Add two properties, 'accumulation-enabled' and 'accumulation-material',
    that controls a new capability of MxOffscreen: Acting as an accumulation
    buffer.
    
    When 'accumulation-enabled' is set to TRUE, MxOffscreen creates an extra
    buffer that it uses as an accumulation buffer. The default settings have
    it blend the primary buffer with the last frame at 50% opacity.
    
    Other effects can be achieved by retrieving the accumulation buffer
    material ('accumulation-material') and changing the blend string.
    
    Addresses MeeGo Bug #2490

 mx/mx-offscreen.c | 225 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 mx/mx-offscreen.h |   6 ++
 2 files changed, 229 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit 812c962c8d05d20c255a3b28d0e3aaf338537828
Author: Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
Date:   Mon May 10 18:24:50 2010 +0100

    offscreen: Provide an accessor for the fbo
    
    Provide an accessor for the off-screen buffer, so that a user may
    manipulate it before it is drawn to. This is required to use MxOffscreen
    as an accumulation buffer, for example.
    
    Fixes MeeGo Bug #1965

 mx/mx-offscreen.c | 108 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--------------------
 mx/mx-offscreen.h |   2 +
 2 files changed, 71 insertions(+), 39 deletions(-)

commit b1a8b5839110663d5ea99343443de465560e36f7
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 1 17:44:14 2010 +0100

    offscreen: Add 'redirect-enabled' property
    
    Add a property, 'redirect-enabled', that lets you bypass
    offscreen-redirection and draw the child directly instead. This is useful
    if you have an effect that you want to turn on and off without having to
    reparent an actor outside of the MxOffscreen.
    
    Based on patch from Chris Lord <chris@linux.intel.com>
    
    Fixes MeeGo Bug #1852

 mx/mx-offscreen.c | 132 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------------
 mx/mx-offscreen.h |   4 ++
 2 files changed, 107 insertions(+), 29 deletions(-)

commit 694f0b194d658e8e94bf0e1f51f2b3262746c01a
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 1 17:00:41 2010 +0100

    table: box-layout: Make spacing settable from CSS
    
    Allow default spacing for table and BoxLayout to be defined in the CSS,
    using -mx-spacing: for BoxLayout and -mx-row-spacing/-mx-column-spacing
    for Table.
    
    Based on patch from iain <iain@linux.intel.com>
    
    Fixes http://bugs.meego.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1331

 mx/mx-box-layout.c | 53 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 mx/mx-table.c      | 60 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 112 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit 361dc21557b0e56e6d344c9faf27a498ce6d298b
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Fri May 28 16:42:59 2010 +0100

    Post release version bump to 1.1.0

 configure.ac | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit 4bdcad11c1a9f62cab76398c51fde7c158f7341e
Author: Thomas Wood <thomas.wood@intel.com>
Date:   Mon May 24 18:11:21 2010 +0100

    widget: move padding into the correct struct
    
    Padding for future expansion of the class should be in the class structure,
    not the instance structure.
    
    Since this changes strict ABI compatibility, the libtool age of the library
    is reduced by adding a binary age offset variable to the configure script.

 configure.ac   |  7 +++++--
 mx/mx-widget.h | 25 +++++++++++++------------
 2 files changed, 18 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)

